            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Kevin Dixon, at 44, rides his bicycle and his life path through the bustling streets of San Francisco. Born and raised in a modest apartment in the Richmond District to immigrant parents from Hong Kong, his upbringing was centered on diligence and practicality. His father worked long hours in a restaurant kitchen, and his mother was a seamstress. Kevin was the middle of three children, learning early the importance of contributing to the household.\n\nHis educational journey was straightforward: Lowell High School, where he excelled in art classes but struggled with more academic subjects. College wasn't a realistic option after graduation; the immediate need to work outweighed the desire for further formal education. He took on various odd jobs \u2013 stock boy, delivery driver \u2013 until a chance encounter led him to a small art gallery in North Beach. Impressed by his willingness to learn and his nascent artistic sensibility, the owner offered him an entry-level position assisting with installations.\n\nThis was a turning point. Kevin discovered a passion for the intricate process of bringing artistic visions to life. He learned to handle delicate pieces, understand spatial relationships, and work alongside skilled professionals. Over the years, he transitioned to larger art installation firms, eventually landing his current role as a Production Assistant, a position offering both creative engagement and a stable income.\n\nHis personal life is quieter. He had a serious relationship in his late twenties but it ended amicably. Currently, his closest connections are work colleagues and a small group of friends he\u2019s known since high school, often meeting for dim sum in the Sunset or catching an independent film. He\u2019s close to his family, still sharing Sunday dinners at his parents' home.\n\nKevin\u2019s hopes are modest but meaningful. He dreams of working on a truly monumental art installation someday, something that will leave a lasting impression on the city he calls home. He also harbors a quiet ambition to create his own art, sketches and small sculptures tucked away in his apartment. His daily routine is a familiar rhythm: the early bike ride to work, the demanding but rewarding day of logistics and physical labor, and quiet evenings spent reading or sketching.\n\nHis connection to San Francisco is deeply ingrained. The city\u2019s diverse energy fuels his creative spirit, and the challenges of living here \u2013 the cost, the competition \u2013 are simply part of its dynamic landscape. He feels most at home in his NoPa neighborhood, the familiar streets and local businesses a comforting constant in a constantly changing city. Kevin Dixon is a quiet but persistent presence, contributing to the city\u2019s artistic pulse, one installation at a time."
